<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-705-542  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 705 542.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Sept 25 1989 v6 n38 p65(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Ask foresees lower earnings for first quarter of fiscal '90. (AskComputer Systems)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   ASK Computer Systems Inc. (earnings).andO;Ticker:    ASKI.andO;Topic:     ProfitFirst Quarter.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   Ask Computer Systems' trailing profits. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Ask Foresees Lower Earnings For First Quarter of Fiscal '90andM;MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif.andP;  -- Officials from MRP II software supplier AskComputer Systems said they expect the company's profits for the first fiscalquarter of 1990 ending Sept. 30 to be &quot;substantially lower&quot; than they were ayear ago, resulting from lower demand and delays in customer approvals forsales.andM;&quot;Delays in the release of hardware products from a number of vendors hascaught up with the manufacturing sector in general, and as a result,customers are delaying their [software] purchasing decisions,&quot; said BradenRippetoe, Ask's treasurer.andP;  &quot;Decision cycles are taking longer.&quot;andM;Rippetoe added that it is too early to tell what kind of impact there will beon fiscal results for the rest of the year.andM;A slow, weak market can be blamed for some of the company's problems,according to Rick Sherlund, vice president of investment research for theinvestment research company Goldman, Sachs in New York.andM;&quot;We're looking at a slowdown in [the] overall midrange market--both DEC andHP have pointed to that,&quot; Sherlund said.andM;When asked about the rate of revenues growth compared to profits, the profitsare &quot;a respectable percentage&quot; of Ask's revenues, said Karen Marvin, Ask'spublic relations manager.andM;Product development, selling and administrative costs as well as the costs ofhardware sold with Ask's software comprise the major costs of the operation,Marvin said.andM;Ask officials said they expect the company to be profitable for the firstquarter of 1990, with revenues equaling the level of the same period lastyear.andM;First-quarter estimates were made prior to Ask's acquisition of Data 3Systems, based in Santa Rosa, Calif., which is scheduled to be finalized thismonth.andM;According to Ask officials, this transaction might have a small positiveimpact on earnings.andM;Officials added that recently announced systems from DEC, as well as thecompany's upcoming move into the IBM market through the Data 3 acquisition,will positively affect the company's market position during the next fewmonths.andO;</TEXT></DOC>